00335 struct ClientId
00336 {
00338     ClientId()
00339     {
00340         memset(m_client_id, 0, MAX_SIZE);
00341     }
00342 
00344     BOOLEAN IsValid()
00345     {
00346         for(INT idx = 0; idx < MAX_SIZE; ++idx)
00347             if(m_client_id[idx] != 0)
00348                 return TRUE;
00349         return FALSE;
00350     }
00351 
00354     void ConvertToStr(String& client_id_str) const
00355     {
00356         // Client Id format:
00357         // m_client_id[0] = n - Size of client id
00358         // m_client_id[1] to m_client_id[n] - Client Id in BCD format
00359         // where each nibble is a binary-coded decimal digit
00360         
00361         // Masks to extract the 2 nibbles of every byte
00362         const BYTE c_lower_nibble = 0x0F;
00363         const BYTE c_upper_nibble = 0xF0;
00364 
00365         // Convert each nibble to a character in order to form the string
00366         BYTE val = 0;
00367         for(UINT16 idx = 1; idx <= m_client_id[0]; idx++) 
00368         {
00369             // Extract the upper nibble of the byte
00370             val = m_client_id[idx] & c_upper_nibble;
00371             val = val >> 4;
00372             client_id_str << val;
00373 
00374             // Extract the lower nibble of the byte
00375             client_id_str << (m_client_id[idx] & c_lower_nibble);
00376         }
00377     }
00378 
00380     enum { MAX_SIZE = 23 };
00381 
00383     BYTE m_client_id[MAX_SIZE];
00384 };

00387 struct ClientName
00388 {
00390     ClientName()
00391     {
00392     }
00393 
00395     ClientName(const BYTE* client_name, Dcs dcs)
00396     {
00397         // The received client name is encoded in 7-bit format and
00398         // packed using USSD packing as per the GSM 03.38 spec Sec 6.
00399         const BYTE c_dcs = 0x0F;
00400         if(dcs != c_dcs)
00401             return;
00402 
00403         // mask
00404         const BYTE c_value_mask_ref = 0x7F;
00405         const BYTE c_carry_mask_ref = 0x80;
00406 
00407         BYTE value_mask = c_value_mask_ref;
00408         BYTE carry_mask = c_carry_mask_ref;
00409         BYTE carry_val = 0;
00410         BYTE temp_val = 0;
00411         UINT16 shift_idx = 0;
00412 
00413         for(UINT16 idx = 0; client_name[idx] != '\0'; idx++)
00414         {
00415             shift_idx = idx % 7;
00416 
00417             temp_val = client_name[idx] & value_mask;
00418             temp_val = temp_val << shift_idx;
00419             temp_val = temp_val | carry_val;
00420 
00421             // Append the value in the string
00422             m_client_name.Insert((m_client_name.GetLength() + 1), temp_val);
00423 
00424             // Update the carry value from this byte
00425             carry_val = (client_name[idx] & carry_mask) >> (7 - shift_idx); 
00426 
00427             // Update the value of value mask and carry mask
00428             value_mask = value_mask >> 1;
00429             carry_mask = carry_mask | (carry_mask >> 1);
00430 
00431             if((shift_idx == 0) && (idx != 0))
00432             {
00433                 temp_val = client_name[idx] & 0xFE;
00434                 temp_val = temp_val >> 1;
00435 
00436                 // Append the value in the string
00437                 m_client_name.Insert((m_client_name.GetLength() + 1), temp_val);
00438 
00439                 value_mask = c_value_mask_ref;
00440                 carry_mask = c_carry_mask_ref;
00441             }
00442         }
00443 
00444     } // Argument Constructor
00445 
00447     enum { MAX_SIZE = 63 };
00448 
00450     String m_client_name;
00451 };
